en promote social justice. The author outlines the new capabilities of genomic science, addresses urgent questions of safety that genetic interventions pose, and explores questions of parenting and justice. He also examines the religious implications of gene modification. Babies by design are assuredly in the future, Green concludes, and by making responsible choices as we enter that future, we can incorporate gene technology in a new age of human adventure.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aGenetic counselingxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aGenetic disorders in childrenxPreventionxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aGenetic engineeringxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aHuman reproductive technologyxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aMedical geneticsxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aPrenatal diagnosisxMoral and ethical aspects. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300138573423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300138573.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles